# Applications — document sync

For every project under `applications/`, final deliverables must live only in each project's `documents/` folder and stay fully in sync across formats. Folder layout is described in `.cursor/rules/folder_structure.mdc`.

## Sync set (per project)

Each project keeps these three deliverables in `documents/`:

| Format      | Filename pattern      |
|-------------|----------------------|
| PDF         | `{project}_pdf.pdf`  |
| PowerPoint  | `{project}_ppt.pptx` |
| Word        | `{project}_word.docx`|

Examples: `awief_pdf.pdf`, `fid_ppt.pptx`, `awief_word.docx`.

## Sync rules

1. If you edit any one of these formats, update the other two in the same session so that narrative, data, branding, and compliance stay fully aligned.
2. Always use **that specific project's** build script(s) for regeneration. Each set must match the requirements of its call — never stamp out multiple projects from a generic template or factory.
3. The most recently edited format should be the main reference for your session. If a project SoT gives a canonical narrative (like AWIEF → `refined_project_idea.md`), use that unless you've edited a different format first. If unsure, check `rules/source_of_truth.mdc`.
4. Never leave the three files out of sync. Do not keep drafts, duplicates, or files with modified names alongside the official documents.
5. Use images and visual assets from the main `assets/` repo (or a project’s own `assets/` subfolder) when regenerating. Keep layout, look, and brand identity consistent across formats.
6. Before finishing updates for an external call, make sure that all synced files meet all eligibility, theme, format, and deadline rules.
7. **PowerPoint slides ({project}_ppt.pptx):** Always make sure the text is sized and balanced properly on every slide for readability and design, taking into account available space, so that your slides look clear and attractive.
8. **Cover / first page:** Include the programme or document title, FairBanks/FCHIP framing, and slogan (**Your health, our mission.**) plus visuals as needed. Only add a summary table with application details on the cover if the official guidelines specifically require it.

## Project-specific sources of truth

- Call rules: `applications/{project}/rules/source_of_truth.mdc`
- Opportunity scan rules: `opportunities/rules/source_of_truth.mdc`

When in doubt, always follow the narrative and compliance from the official call. Only keep one rules tree per project — no duplicate copies. Project sources of truth are set with globs (not always-on), so AWIEF, FID, and opportunities rules never override each other.
